<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE>Public Conferences</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<H2><CENTER>PUBLIC CONFERENCES<BR>
<HR></CENTER>
</H2>
In order to further extend the impact of the George Washington Fellows program,
Discovery Institute sponsored two public conferences in conjunction with
last year's seminar. The Fellows attended these conferences and interacted
with the guest speakers.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
The first public event was a two-night conference on &quot;The Death of
Materialism&quot; held at Seattle Pacific University on July 19 and 20.
Co-sponsored with the Shuv Institute and the Intercollegiate Studies Institute,
the conference examined the debilitating consequences of materialism on
western society and on new developments in physics, biology, and cognitive
science that are undermining the basis of materialism. Speakers included
Stephen Meyer of Discovery Institute and Whitworth College, George Gilder
of Discovery Institute, Paul Vitz of New York University, and John Campbell
of the University of Washington (now at the University of Memphis). More
than 100 people attended the event, and portions of the conference were
played on cable television throughout Washington state. This spring the
national journal <I>Intercollegiate Review</I> will publish a symposium
based on the papers given at the conference with an introduction by Discovery
Senior Fellow John West. <I>Intercollegiate Review</I> is distributed quarterly
to more than 55,000 faculty and students at colleges and universities across
America. <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
In addition to the &quot;Death of Materialism&quot; conference, a public
luncheon seminar was held on July 28 that examined the implications of the
landmark equal access decision in Rosenberger vs. the Rector and Visitors
of the University of Virginia. The seminar featured law professor and Discovery
Institute Senior Fellow Edward Larson, Perkins Coie attorney Randy Beck,
and national ACLU board member Judith Bendich. The presentations by Larson
and Beck have been adapted for publication as a <I>Discovery Institute Inquiry</I>
paper.<BR>
<P><CENTER><A HREF="1995gwf.html"><IMG SRC="dymored-back.gif" WIDTH="78"
HEIGHT="17" ALIGN="BOTTOM" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></A></CENTER>
