<HEAD>
    <TITLE>Guest Speakers</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<H2><CENTER>GUEST FACULTY AND SPEAKERS<BR>
<HR></CENTER>
</H2>
In addition to the regular daily sessions, the Fellows participated in special
seminars on selected topics with Discovery Senior Fellows and other guest
speakers: 
<UL>
  <LI>Former Attorney General Edwin Meese held a private question-and-answer
session with Fellows about faith and public life. <BR>
<BR>
  <LI>Discovery Senior Fellow and author George Gilder held a private question-and-answer
session with Fellows on issues relating to faith, ethics, and economics.<BR>
<BR>
  <LI>Discovery Senior Fellow Dr. Stephen Meyer of Whitworth College discussed
academic freedom for people of faith and shared how new scientific developments
are refuting the ideology of scientific naturalism. <BR>
<BR>
  <LI>Discovery Senior Fellow Dr. Edward Larson of the University of Georgia
and Discovery Institute gave a behind-the-scenes account of the passage
of the landmark Equal Access Act. He also gave a presentation on the ethical
implications of the human genome project and developments in genetics. <BR>
<BR>
  <LI>Adam Pruzan of Discovery Institute delivered a presentation about
modern Judaism and politics in America. 
</UL>
