<P>
<li> There were a few isolated problems
with natural gas tanks or cylinders as they are called, but these
seem to have been rectified. CNG tanks are fairly rugged.  Several
tests show no fuel being released in a 50 mph rear-end collision
or in drop tests.  Automatic shutoff valves react if a line ruptures
preventing full dispersion of the tank's contents.  A pressure
relief valve allows gas to escape in the event of an external
fire, reducing the chance of an explosion. 
<P>
<li> For a complete discussion of the
safety concerns for the use of CNG, methanol, and electric vehicles,
see U.S. Department of Energy, <U>Assessment of Costs and Benefits
of Flexible and Alternative Fuel Use in the U.S. Transportation
Sector: Technical Report Seven: Environmental, Health, and Safety
