<li> We note that some flexibility currently
exists in the interpretation of emissions for new sources in nonattainment
areas when those sources, by law, are involved in trading transactions
with existing sources.  Reitze pointed out in 1991 that 22 states
use regulator-determined emission allowances as the baseline;
8 states use the lower of allowable or actual emissions from sources;
8 states use &quot;variable baselines for different kinds of emission
trades; four states use actual emissions&quot; and 8 states had
no information available on the topic. (Arnold W. Reitze, Jr.,
&quot;A Century of Air Pollution Control Law: What's Worked; What's
Failed; What Might Work,&quot; <U>Environmental Law</U>, Vol.
