</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">*See text for calculations.<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT FACE="Arial">We conclude this analysis by noting an underlying
issue that explains why emission reductions are so costly.  Vehicle
emissions are at a very low level, which means that a large number
of vehicles must be affected to generate annually a ton of emission
reductions.  On the basis of the EPA data we used, CNG vehicles
emit 5.7 pounds of VOCs annually.  Ethanol and methanol blends
emit 26.5 pounds, and RFG-fueled vehicles emit 61.7 pounds.  A
conventional vehicle using standard gasoline emits 77.2 pounds
of VOCs each year.</FONT>
<P>
<a href="sect5.html">Next Section: Emerging AFV Niche Markets</a><p>
<a href="sect3.html">Previous Section: Economic Incentives For The Production of Cleaner Air</a><p>
