<title>AOL problems</title>



<h5><a href="/townhall/aol.html.cgi/textonly">[Text View]</a></h5>

<p>
<h3>America Online&#174; Users</h3>
please note. There seems to be a particular problem with some AOL
accounts. The problem is that information is not getting passed from
the client (browser) to the server correctly. The result is that
after completing a form and pressing <i>submit</i>, the information
in the form is not passed to the server correctly, and the server
reports that the form is incomplete. This is not a general problem
with AOL, since many AOL users have successfully completed the forms
and submitted them. In is unknown at this time if the problem is with
a particular version of the AOL browser, or a proxy server that AOL
users go through.
<p>
If you experience this problem please contact AOL.
<p>



<a href="/townhall/apply.html.cgi">Return</a>

to the application form.
