crumbling buildings in the inner city neighborhood near the school may 
say "quit," Mrs.. Collins teaches her students that "can't" is just "can" 
without the "t." Every child in here will tell you we do not take average 
papers. We tell them average people are never in short supply.  If we 
strive for excellence, we can become all that we want to become.
